==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sciagraph
<hw>Sci"a*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sciagraphy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>An old
term for a vertical section of a building; -- called also
<altname>sciagraphy</altname>. See <cref>Vertical section</cref>, under
<er>Section</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phys.)</fld> <def>A radiograph.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>skiagraph</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sciagraphical</ent>⟦br⟧
